===[ Data Matrix & Frequency Table ]===

# REVISION:============================================
# - case is one unit of observation (person or thing).|
# - varibales are the characteristic of the case.     | 
# =====================================================

* Data Matrix & Frequency Table are 'foundational tools for organizing and'
  'summarizing data'.

  > [ Data Matrix: ]
    * is a structured format for storing raw data, typically in rows and columns
      where: 
      . Columns: varibales 
      . Rows: cases 

  > [ Examples: ]
    _________________________________
    | Person | Age | Gender | Score |
    |--------|-----|--------|-------|
    | 1      | 23  | M      | 88    |
    | 2      | 30  | F      | 92    |
    | 3      | 25  | M      | 85    |
    |________|_____|________|_______|

    . rows: cases (person 1, person 2 ...)
    . columns: varibales (Age, Gender and Score)  

> [ Table Frequency: (Frequency: ÿ™ŸÉÿ±ÿßÿ±)]
  - It simplifies the large datasets by 'summarizes' how each value or category
    of a varibale occurs. 

  |> Usage:
      . Simplfies large datasets
      . Identifies patterns, trends, or outliers 
      . Helps visualize the distribution of data
        => Often used with historgrams or bar charts
      . Enables quick calculation of:
        - Mode 
        - Relative Frequency
        - Comulative frequency 

  > [ Examples: ] 
    _________________________________________________
    | Grade | Frequency | Percentage %| Cumulative %|
    |-------|-----------|-------------|-------------|
    | A     | 10        |    28       |    28       |
    | B     | 15        |    43       |    71       |
    | C     | 8         |    23       |    94       |
    | D     | 2         |     6       |    100      |
    |_______|___________|_____________|_____________|
    | Total |   35      |   100%      |    100%     | 

# NOTE:========================================================================
# - Matrix table is the source to start the anaylsis
# - Frequency table is good to display the data where we can provide summary
#   for the dataset
# - You can use the ghraphs to summarize the data
# ==============================================================================

